-- Egypt Needs New Democatic Era, South Africa's Ntsaluba Says, M&G Reports
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2011-02-04T07:08:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-04/egypt-needs-new-democatic-era-south-africa-s-ntsaluba-says-m-g-reports.html
  Egypt  needs to “usher in a new era”
based on democracy, Ayanda Ntsaluba,  South Africa ’s director
general of international relations and cooperation, said in an
interview, the Mail & Guardian newspaper reported.  The “status quo” can’t remain in terms of the government
and the unrest in the country shows that the outcome of
elections is questionable, according to the Johannesburg-based
newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
